HEADWORD: Undercroft
<hw>Un"der*croft</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Under</ets>
+ Prov. E. <ets>croft</ets> a vault; cf. OD. <ets>krochte</ets> crypt,
and E. <ets>crypt</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A subterranean
room of any kind; esp., one under a church (see <er>Crypt</er>), or one
used as a chapel or for any sacred purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

